<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[French rapper MHD jailed for 12 years over Paris murder]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/24/french-rapper-mhd-jailed-for-12-years-over-paris]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-24T02:24:12Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/12f5179345ad1b9185dafecdb68f5b97b0a3989a/202_144_4293_2576 /master/4293.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ee466f3fbc64b1bd59acc15f97e13bcb&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;法国说唱歌手 MHD，真名 Mohamed Sylla，本月出庭&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;法国说唱歌手 MHD 有因 2018 年在巴黎谋杀一名年轻男子而被判处 12 年监禁，这名年轻男子在被暴徒袭击并被刺伤之前被一辆汽车撞死。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他的五名同案被告也因谋杀罪被判入狱。检察官称这是敌对帮派之间的斗殴事件，并被判处 10 至 18 年徒刑。另外三名男子被无罪释放。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;被定罪的人（均不不认罪）有 10 天的时间提出上诉。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在 MHD 向法院做出最后陈述期间，该机构退休后考虑其判决。经过三周的诉讼，他再次表示自己是无辜的。他在挤满人的法庭上说：“从一开始，我在这起案件中就一直坚称自己无罪，并将继续坚称自己无罪。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;2018 年 7 月 5 日晚，23 岁的卢瓦克 (Loic) K 在法国首都第十区被一辆黑色奔驰撞倒，然后被十几个人殴打并刺伤。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;MHD 的真名是穆罕默德·西拉 (Mohamed Sylla)，他否认曾在现场，但一名当地居民从他的窗户拍摄了这一事件，这辆奔驰车被确认属于 MHD。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;根据调查报告，其他目击者通过他的发型或 Puma 的运动衫（他是 Puma 的品牌大使）认出了 MHD。法新社看到。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;凶杀案发生一天后，这辆车被发现被遗弃并在停车场被烧毁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;MHD 开创了非洲式陷阱 - 一种嘻哈风格的混合体啤酒花和非洲传统——并在 2015 年引起轰动后声名鹊起。这位 29 岁的男子于 2019 年 1 月被指控犯有杀人罪并入狱。在调查继续进行期间，他被拘留一年半后被释放，并发行了一张新专辑。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六的判决宣布后，公共旁听席上的几位女性泪流满面。 MHD 拥抱了其中一人，保持镇静。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;受害人家属律师朱丽叶特·查佩尔 (Juliette Chapelle) 表示：“尽管有沉默法则，司法真相还是浮出水面。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;检察官要求判处这位说唱歌手 18 年监禁，两名被告无罪释放，其他被告判处 13 至 20 年监禁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;凶杀案发生在 Cite des Chaufourniers 庄园，这位前披萨外卖司机尽管名声大噪，但仍经常光顾该地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位狂热的足球表演者出生在法国，父母是几内亚人和塞内加尔人，他因非洲陷阱第 3 部分（欧洲冠军联赛）而闻名。 ），一首赞美巴黎圣日耳曼足球俱乐部的歌曲。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他在国外掀起了波澜，赢得了德雷克和麦当娜等全球明星的钦佩。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 10:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Pacific summit suffers setback as Solomon Islands PM skips meeting]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/24/biden-pacific-summit-suffers-setback-as-solomon-islands-pm-skips-meeting]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-24T02:09:22Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/28e930068e018b36547ea8014e52c598c60f55f5/218_9_3282_2258 /master/3282.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=268abe5ba682a6abba0bc07b00fca7ce&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;所罗门群岛总理玛纳西·索加瓦雷周五在纽约联合国大会上发表讲话&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;白宫表示，对所罗门群岛总理玛纳西·索加瓦雷无法出席下周与乔·拜登举行的太平洋岛屿峰会感到失望。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国总统将与太平洋领导人举行第二次峰会周一在白宫举行的岛屿论坛是他加强与美国正在与中国争夺影响力的地区接触的努力的一部分。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们对所罗门群岛总理索加瓦雷不这样做感到失望拜登政府官员表示：“我不打算参加。”国家需求”，并表示北京是其主要基础设施合作伙伴。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023 /aug/02/solomon-islands-newspaper-pledged-to-promote-truth-about-chinas-generosity-in-return-for-funding&quot;>;所罗门群岛报纸承诺宣传“关于中国慷慨的真相”以换取资金&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;索加瓦雷表示，他在7月访华期间与习近平主席达成共识，希望所罗门群岛通过中国的政策，包括“一带一路”倡议实现发展和全球安全倡议。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另外，中国和东帝汶宣布将双边关系提升为全面战略伙伴关系，这可能会赋予北京在该地区更大的影响力。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该协议达成北京周六表示，习近平在亚运会开幕式前夕在中国东部城市杭州会见了东帝汶总理夏纳纳·古斯芒。习近平表示：“双方将加大相互支持，加强国际合作。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;199069daca2587b877a0511b63d2559b3b9f3403&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/199069daca2587b877a0511b63d2559b3b9f340 3 /51_240_3099_1860/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;所罗门群岛总理玛纳西·索加瓦雷与中国国家主席习近平七月在北京会晤&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;所罗门群岛总理玛纳西·索加瓦雷（左）和中国国家主席习近平七月在北京会面。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：路透社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;去年，何塞·拉莫斯-奥尔塔 (Jose Ramos-Horta) 就任总统时这位诺贝尔奖获得者是东帝汶自 2002 年独立以来的第五任总统，他承诺与中国建立更密切的关系，特别是在能源、农业和基础设施领域。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;为了升级两国关系，中国和东帝汶同意在习近平倡导的“一带一路”倡议可以为基础设施投资开辟道路。东帝汶还计划在2030年左右开始从其Greater Sunrise油田生产天然气，希望开发这个陷入困境数十年的海上项目。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;双方同意进行密切的高层军事互动周六发布的联合声明称，扩大双边投资以及基础设施和食品等领域的合作。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拜登与 18 名论坛成员的太平洋峰会将于周一和周二在华盛顿举行。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据澳大利亚广播公司 ABC 报道，所罗门群岛外交部长杰里米亚·马内莱 (Jeremiah Manele) 将出席峰会。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;所罗门群岛总理办公室没有对路透社做出回应瓦努阿图总理萨托基尔曼办公室的一名官员周五表示，瓦努阿图总理萨托基尔曼也不会出席会议，因为所有瓦努阿图政府立法者都需要在周一出席议会，以寻求不-信任投票。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 10:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘I am willing to wait for months’: Chinese Tiananmen critic ready for long haul in Taiwan transit lounge]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/24/china-dissident-taiwan-chen-siming-willing-to-wait-airport-transit-lounge-tiananmen]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-24T01:05:08Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7c6e422e326cc52750fe7018404e247eeb6f67d5/0_0_3000_2000 /master/3000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=96fa04e8bdc6db51d39ca6880a62faf5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;中国异议人士程思明躲在台湾桃园国际机场的转机休息室。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;一名在中途停留期间在台湾机场避难的中国异见人士表示，如果需要，他准备等待数月，以便安全前往第三国。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;陈思明因定期纪念而闻名。 1989 年 6 月 4 日的天安门广场大屠杀——这一事件在中国境内被禁止讨论或承认——并在周年纪念日前后多次被拘留。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href =&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/13/china-unveils-taiwan-economic-integration-plan-as-warships-conduct-manoeuvres-off-coast&quot;>;中国公布台湾经济&#39;战舰在近海进行演习时的整合计划&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;在他的&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world 后不久发布到社交媒体上的视频中/2023/sep/22/chinese-dissident-tiananmen-square-vigils-flees-taiwan-chen-siming&quot;>;周五抵达台湾&lt;/a>;陈说，最近当局针对他的攻击“更加频繁”更加残酷和疯狂”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他现在请求台湾政府协助他在第三国（最好是美国）重新定居，并称他的“情况危险而紧急”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我愿意等待几个月，因为我在台湾感到安全，”陈告诉卫报。 “我想去美国。我觉得台湾很安全，不存在安全问题。台湾有民主自由作为庇护所，所以台湾对我个人来说是安全的。但安全并不是我定居的第一选择，我在美国还有很多工作要做。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;陈周五从泰国飞往中国广州，经台北桃园国际机场转机。他没有登上第二架航班，并拒绝返回泰国的请求，他说他担心被驱逐到中国。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;安全不是我定居的第一选择，我在美国还有很多工作要做。&lt;/p>; &lt;footer>; &lt;cite>;陈思明&lt;/cite>; &lt;/footer>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;类似的案例表明陈可以需要等待一段时间。 2018年至2019年，两名中国异见人士严伯钧和刘兴联同样从泰国飞抵台湾，并拒绝重新搭乘飞往北京的航班，他们在台湾机场过境区度过了四个月。联合国难民事务高级专员办事处（UNHCR）给予他们临时庇护身份，在长期僵局之后，两人飞往新加坡，然后获准以短期人道主义签证合法重新进入台湾。他们最终在加拿大定居。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;陈告诉《卫报》，他于 7 月从中国逃往老挝，但在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com 后，朋友们敦促他离开。 /world/2023/aug/03/rights-groups-laos-release-lawyer-china-lu-siwei&quot;>;当月晚些时候，人权律师卢四伟在当地被捕&lt;/a>;。在曼谷，他向联合国难民署登记进行难民评估，并表示他很快就获得了为期一年的庇护身份。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;国际特赦组织台湾分部主任邱伊玲呼吁台湾政府允许陈出机场进入台湾并协助他转机到第三国。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;21598bf528af3838e55c390d587316cafae1f284&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/ 21598bf528af3838e55c390d587316cafae1f284/0_279_5000_3002/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;当天，湖南省陈思明坐在写有“纪念2021年6月4日6月4日”的告示旁烛光&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600 ” >; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;当天，中国中部湖南省陈思明坐在写着“2021年6月4日纪念6月4日”的告示旁。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：美联社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Chiu 表示，台湾当局此前已将寻求庇护者驱逐回最后的出发地。 “如果台湾政府采取驱逐立场，他们可以将他送回泰国，”她说。 “但如果他们将他驱逐回中国，那就违反了不驱回原则。这是不可接受的。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;处理台湾与中国事务的台湾陆委会告诉《卫报》，他们正在处理滞留异议人士的案件，但没有提供更多细节。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;台湾没有提供保护途径的难民计划，但它已将非法抵达寻求政治庇护的行为合法化。在台湾，简化难民程序的前景在政治上充满了担忧，政党和公众都担心中国的渗透和间谍活动。支持者表示，像其他国家一样，适当和透明的流程将对申请人进行背景调查。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是对中国威胁的恐惧，但[没有系统]并不是一个合理的解决方案”邱说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;中国人权捍卫者组织的研究和倡导协调员倪威廉表示，“很多人迫切希望离开中国”，并指出了陈的危险旅程。和卢进入对北京友好的老挝，以及&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/mar/09/forming-numbers-of-chinese-citizens-set-their-sights-on- the-us-via-the-deadly-darien-gap&quot;>;越来越多的中国人穿越南美洲和中美洲之间的达连海峡&lt;/a>;，进入墨西哥，然后进入美国。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;台湾倪说，政府需要与其他国家“建设性地合作”，为陈寻求保护。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;已联系在台湾没有办事处的联合国难民署征求意见。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 09:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Dozens of Met officers refuse armed patrols after colleague’s murder charge]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/23/dozens-of-met-officers-refuse-armed-patrols-after-colleagues-charge]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T20:44:31Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4386b5df02617a99a6d707bdf7ed516a035d49d0/0_53_5257_3155 /master/5257.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=cbd6bfec0b32596d65e72932f8b9fd00&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;2023 年，伯克郡温莎，武装警察进入巡逻车&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;数十名大都会警察在一名同事被指控谋杀后，警察枪械官员拒绝外出武装巡逻。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;70 多名警察射手表示，他们需要时间考虑是否仍愿意携带枪支他们的同事面临谋杀指控。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其他人拒绝外出进行定期武装巡逻，并留在自己的岗位上，而另一些人则表示，他们只会在紧急情况下做出反应。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;去年 9 月，一名仅被确认为 NX121 的武装军官被指控谋杀了克里斯·卡巴 (Chris Kaba)。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;24 岁的卡巴 (Kaba) 在伦敦东南部的斯特里汉姆山 (Streatham Hill) 去世，此前他被谋杀。在武装拦截期间被汽车挡风玻璃射穿。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该警官已获得有条件保释，预计明年将接受审判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在上周提出谋杀指控之前，只有五名警官被判有条件保释。据信是被指控警官的亲密同事的神枪手已经归还了他们的“蓝票”——之所以这么称呼，是因为向经过培训和授权的警官发放的个人枪支许可证的尺寸和颜色。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;高级包括大都会专员马克·罗利爵士在内的官员们已经会见了枪械小组，讨论了指控其同事谋杀罪的决定的影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;苏格兰场表示：“包括专员在内的高级官员已经最近几天，他们一直在与枪械官员会面，反思皇家检察署指控 NX121 谋杀罪的决定。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“许多官员在考虑自己的立场时决定退出武装职责。这个数字在过去 48 小时内有所增加。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们正在与这些官员进行持续讨论，以支持他们并充分理解他们真正关心的问题。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;气象局已向周边部队通报情况，并在出现问题时通过互助制度请求帮助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据了解，机场、皇室和外交保护以及议会的枪支覆盖不会受到影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; p>; &lt;p>;“大都会拥有强大的枪支能力，我们继续在伦敦各地的社区以及议会、外交场所、机场等其他地点部署武装人员。我们的首要任务是确保公众安全。警方表示，我们正在密切关注事态发展，并在需要时探索应急方案。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周日，在卡迪夫举行的警察阵亡将士纪念日仪式上，我们将向 Suella Braverman 提出这一情况，以向警官致敬。因公殉职的人。据了解，内政大臣和她的官员正在密切关注事态发展。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在与枪支官员会面后，罗利表示：“他们的焦虑是可以理解的，因为他们考虑到其他人可能会在数年之后如何评估他们的瞬间决定。”活动，他们有尽可能多的时间来做这件事，以及这可能对他们和他们的家人产生的影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他们不仅准备好对抗武装分子和危险分子，以保护伦敦的安全社区，但他们这样做认识到他们将在瞬间的运营决策中面临独特的强烈和漫长的个人责任。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“事实上，我理解为什么他们中的许多人正在反思如此重大责任的潜在代价。勇敢有多种形式。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当警官们像我今天在同事身上看到的那样充满不确定性和担忧时，只要投入工作，不知道前方会发生什么事件，就是勇敢的。 ”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 07:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[US agrees to send long-range missiles to Ukraine in military boost for Kyiv]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/23/us-agrees-to-send-long-range-missiles-atacms-to-ukraine-in-military-boost-for-kyiv]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T17:23:18Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/0c68de38fc728044bc1a0d4d5f3d42fde6bea492/0_117_3500_2100 /master/3500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=813e9567d23aa0644dca2272bd644823&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;夜间从发射器发射 ATACMS 导弹&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;美国总统乔·拜登已决定向乌克兰提供远程陆军战术导弹系统（ATACMS），这将在该国为第二个战争冬天做准备之际，极大地增强基辅远距离瞄准俄罗斯军事后勤的能力。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拜登告诉乌克兰国家电视台据美国全国广播公司 (NBC) 援引美国官员的话报道，乌克兰领导人弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基 (Volodymyr Zelenskiy) 在一次私人会议上表示，将转移少量武器。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乌克兰几个月来一直要求提供 ATACMS。美国官员不愿意这样做，因为该国自己的库存有限，并且担心俄罗斯可能指责华盛顿升级局势。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但乌克兰将承诺不会用它们瞄准俄罗斯领土，并放弃允许转移集群的权利据&lt;em>;华尔街日报&lt;/em>;报道，向乌克兰提供的弹药增加了那里可能使用的潜在导弹的数量。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;ATACMS 从移动发射器发射，可以击中 190 英里外的目标（300公里）外，使乌克兰军队能够远远超出前线进行打击。潜在目标包括指挥总部、武器库和包括铁路在内的供应网络。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当被问及有关拜登改变立场的报道时，泽连斯基没有直接回应，仅表示美国是乌克兰最大的武器供应国。报道称。“我们正在讨论所有不同类型的武器——远程武器和火炮、155毫米口径的炮弹，然后是防空系统，”泽连斯基在对加拿大进行正式访问期间的新闻发布会上表示。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;乌克兰购买 ATACMS 是一场长期且基本成功的运动中的最新一次，该运动旨在推动西方盟国获取更先进的武器，而乌克兰在地面上取得的军事成功也为这一运动提供了支持。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当俄罗斯入侵时去年，制导反坦克导弹是运往乌克兰的高科技装备之一。它现在拥有西方坦克、地对空导弹防御系统和训练有素的飞行员来接管 F-16 战斗机机队。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/jun/01/himars-what-are-the-advanced-rockets-us-is-sending-ukraine&quot;>;Himars：美国先进的火箭是什么正在发送乌克兰吗？ &lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;随着美国去年开始转让这些系统，乌克兰军队已经熟悉用于发射 ATACMS 的希马尔斯移动火箭发射器。然而，它只向乌克兰提供了短程制导火箭弹。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;远程导弹在冬季可能尤其重要，因为寒冷的天气会减缓前线的战斗，而俄罗斯可能会试图加强其防御能力。占领乌克兰领土。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乌克兰发动了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/02/ukraine-counter-offective-rust-war&quot; title=&quot; “今年夏天的反攻进展比该国自己的军队及其美国盟友所希望的要慢&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;基辅的目标是突破俄罗斯的防线，然后深入亚速海，孤立俄罗斯赫尔松周围的入侵部队并切断了克里米亚的补给路线。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，事实证明，即使是美国和欧洲列强的装甲车和坦克也无法穿透，密集的地雷带使部队陷入了数周的停滞。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;最终，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/02/everything-is-ahead-of-us-ukraine-breaks-Russias-first 清理出了一条道路-line-of-defence-in-stronghold&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;徒步工兵&lt;/a>;，上周，装甲车突破了俄罗斯在同一地区的主要反坦克防御，这是另一项重大突破。他们可以更轻松地向南推进，或者从后方沿防线攻击俄罗斯军队。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;虽然地面攻势进展缓慢，但乌克兰一直试图利用远程无人机和其他武器向俄罗斯军队施加压力。攻击发生在俄罗斯境内和被占领的乌克兰领土上，特别是克里米亚。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管泽连斯基上周旋风般访问华盛顿期间没有就 ATACMS 发表正式声明，但他获得了 3.25 亿美元的美国新援助，并致力于加强政治家对乌克兰的支持。虽然在欧洲，对乌克兰战争努力的支持主要是两党共同支持的，但在美国，党派政治路线上存在分歧，存在&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis. com/international/lists/tag/us-news/republicans&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;国会共和党派&lt;/a>;在很大程度上与该党总统候选人唐纳德·特朗普保持一致，后者越来越反对资助援助和武器转让。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 07:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Florida authorities find 13ft alligator in canal with human remains in mouth]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/23/florida-13ft-alligator-human-remains]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T19:09:50Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/43f44ecf15fb2990c2df47172df90703a5d1befb/0_182_6000_3600 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f7472c17bc3a308b2922c701dc073943&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;鳄鱼头从水中露出&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;当局对一条 13 英尺长、嘴里含着人类遗骸的鳄鱼实施了安乐死周五下午，这只动物出现在佛罗里达州拉戈市的一条运河中。 .&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;皮内拉斯县治安官办公室在一份新闻稿中表示，这只雄性鳄鱼身高 13 英尺 8.5 英寸，在被从水中捞出后被“人道”杀死。治安官的潜水队从水道中打捞出人类遗骸。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/ 2023/jul/16/florida-man-survives-alligator-bite&quot;>;佛罗里达州 79 岁男子被鳄鱼咬伤后幸存：“有很多皮肤被撕掉”&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;代表们没有透露调查人员是否相信鳄鱼杀死了尸体在鳄鱼嘴里的人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;致命的鳄鱼袭击事件很少见。根据在线动物百科&lt;a href=&quot;https://az-animals.com/blog/alligator-attacks-do-alligators-eat-people/&quot;>;AZ Animals，&lt;/a>;平均有大约美国每年报告六起致命的鳄鱼袭击事件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.clickorlando.com/pets/2021/07/13/what-you-need-to-know -about-alligator-laws-in-florida/&quot;>;佛罗里达州栖息着超过 100 万只鳄鱼&lt;/a>;。在过去 10 年里，佛罗里达州&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tcpalm.com/story/news/local/2023/02/21/alligator-attack-florida-gator-kills-boy-disney-how -many-attacks-are-there-what-should-you-do-bitten/69926522007/&quot;>;平均每年&lt;/a>;发生约八起鳄鱼无端咬伤事件，需要就医。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Jamarcus布拉德在周五下午向当地 NBC 新闻附属机构发表讲话时描述了发现鳄鱼的情况。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我向鳄鱼扔了一块石头，只是想看看它是否真的是鳄鱼，就像它拉动了身体一样 - 就像它一样抓住躯干的下半部分并将其拉到水下，”他说。布拉德随后用手机记录了鳄鱼的情况，并将其提供给当局。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;调查人员表示，他们正在对尸体与鳄鱼在一起的人进行尸检，以确定死因。据官员称，死者的身份也尚未确定。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot; _blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 03:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Rishi Sunak pushes to axe northern HS2 rail line ahead of Tory conference]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/23/rishi-sunak-pushes-to-axe-northern-hs2-rail-line-ahead-of-tory-conference]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T18:14:36Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e64f5ab6f60c3a935831afebb56bfff87c447084/25_164_3949_2370 /master/3949.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=3ccc086399ac84af8391fab273a19ad5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;穿越乡村背景的 HS2 地面工程&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Rishi Sunak 面临着高层的强烈反对保守党和商界领袖有迹象表明，他准备在下周末曼彻斯特保守党会议开幕之前废除 HS2 高速铁路线的北段。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;多位消息人士告诉《观察家报》。周六，首相和财政大臣杰里米·亨特定于周一或周二举行会议，苏纳克将在本周中旬宣布决定。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一消息人士称，任何取消 HS2 从伯明翰至曼彻斯特路段的决定都无法在会议上做出，必须在会议之前做出。 “他必须在保守党去曼彻斯特之前做到这一点。要做到这一点，那是不可思议的。这对这座城市来说将是一次沉重的打击。因此，提前这样做似乎是计划。”周六晚上，有迹象表明商界领袖正在轰炸 10 号，要求不要废弃北区，有强烈的传言称至少有一名中层 -如果该项目大幅削减，高级部长可能会辞职。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另一位支持 HS2 的部长明确表示他会感到震惊。 “我不能谈论它。我不想再提了。我的立场长期以来一直很明确。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一位消息人士表示，苏纳克可能会临阵退缩并决定不取消伯明翰至曼彻斯特的航线，这“并非不可想象”。唐宁街拒绝发表评论，只是表示仍致力于 HS2，尽管这将涵盖其对伦敦至伯明翰线的支持。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;HS2 掉头的消息是在苏纳克几天后发布的 &lt;a href =&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/20/rishi-sunak-confirms-rollback-of-key-green-targets&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;扭转了一系列气候危机政策&lt;/ a>;，包括将销售新汽油和柴油汽车的禁令从 2030 年推迟到 2035 年，因为他试图在大选前与工党划定新的“分界线”。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span >;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/18/hs2-manchester-andy-burnham-rishi-sunak-birmingham&quot;>;构建 HS2，北方领导人表示，部长们拒绝确认曼彻斯特的联系&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;周六晚上，大曼彻斯特工党市长安迪·伯纳姆 (Andy Burnham) 表示，如果 HS2 不修建到曼彻斯特，那么这也将敲响新的东西向铁路线的丧钟，保守党长期以来一直承诺将其作为其升级议程的一部分。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伯纳姆说：“通往曼彻斯特的 HS2 建设了新东-西铁路线的核心。”西线称为北方动力站铁路。如果政府取消 HS2 的建设，他们也将取消这条新的东西向线路以及整个北部地区的建设。我们将保留维多利亚时代的铁路基础设施，而该国的南半部将由新的高速线路连接起来。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“在议会结束时，本意是让我们变得更加平等，保守党将成功地为南北分歧进一步扩大奠定基础。随着政治背叛的进行，它不会变得更大。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据接近 HS2 项目的人士称，苏纳克长期以来一直不喜欢该项目，并且比亨特更反对建设北部部分。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;两位前首相戴维·卡梅伦和鲍里斯·约翰逊都明确表示反对缩减 HS2 项目，这将是保守党执政 13 年来为数不多的知名基础设施项目之一。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;越来越多的人认为，作为进一步削减成本的措施，HS2 将不会按计划运行至尤斯顿站。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;本周末，伦敦市长萨迪克·汗 (Sadiq Khan) 致信苏纳克说，如果是这样的话，乘坐现有线路从伦敦到伯明翰的旅程将比提议的新线路更快。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;汗写道：“政府对 HS2 的做法有可能浪费巨大的经济机会他补充道：“终止 Old Oak Common 的服务将是一个短视的决定，这将产生长期影响，大大降低 HS2 作为高水平铁路的价值。”速度连接并留下一个荒谬的情况，即伯明翰和伦敦市中心之间的“高速”旅程可能需要与现有路线一样长的时间，甚至更长。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;《观察家报》理解整个白厅，包括财政部内部，都担心切断伯明翰以外的线路会破坏该项目的商业案例。一位白厅消息人士警告称，缩减规模将使其成为“无能的象征”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一位内部人士表示：“即使是财政部官员实际上也有点担心供应链影响以及取消如此大规模的影响。无论是在国内还是在国际上，承诺和表现方式都是如此。”消息人士还表示，缩减该额度所带来的任何节省在短期内都不会帮助苏纳克，也不会筹集到可用于选举前减税的大量资金。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一位白厅消息人士表示：“如果不这样做尤斯顿大学和伯明翰大学，整个项目的经济效益并不相称。事实上，它可能不再物有所值。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在上周出现一系列大转变和新的政策想法之后，政府中的一些人表示，决策似乎是根据Sunak 的个人喜好，包括他长期以来对 HS2 和 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/sep/22/rishi-sunak-considers-banning-香烟-for-next-周六，《卫报》表示，第十号正在研究有效禁止年轻人购买香烟的措施。 “这是制定政策的一个奇怪的基础，”一位资深保守党人士表示。 “净零排放、吸烟、A-level 改革——除了他的个人观点之外，是什么将这些事情联系在一起？”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;白厅越来越多的人认为，10 号正在推动一系列激进的政策转变，以解决这两个问题。与工党划清界限，并对苏纳克总理职位做出明确界定。许多人认为这是为明年 5 月的大选做准备。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;与此同时，在出现&lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/23/uk-ministers-scrap-energy-efficiency-taskforce-after-six-months&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;加快家庭隔热和锅炉升级的工作组已解散&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;气候变化委员会首席执行官克里斯·斯塔克（Chris Stark）独立为政府提供咨询，他质疑这是否标志着政府结束将英国能源总需求减少 15% 的目标。 2030 年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“该工作组由来自商业和金融部门的重要人士组成，为实现这一目标提供建议。”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;杰森·麦卡特尼 (Jason McCartney)，科恩谷 (Colne Valley) 保守党议员西约克郡表示，如果 HS2 和北方发电站铁路没有全面建成，这对北方将是一个巨大的打击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我是两者的大力支持者。它们将创造数千个就业机会并提供急需的连通性。我们需要双方都支持这些项目。需要真正的跨党派承诺。”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color: orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https: //feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 02:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Dozens killed and injured by truck bomb explosion in Somalian city]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/23/dozens-killed-and-wounded-by-truck-bomb-explosion-in-beledweyne-somalia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T17:34:43Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7708ce29e29ef8e239309b99dbf7bdff5a7d828f/0_216_1961_1177/master/1961.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=d5a23f177849d926834ef4d415511bab&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;large amount of smoke bilowing in the sky above Beledweyne, Somalia&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;An explosives-laden vehicle has detonated at a security checkpoint in the central Somalia city of Beledweyne on Saturday, killing at least 18 people and wounding 40 others, authorities have said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Abdirahman Dahir Gure, the interior minister of Hirshabelle state, announced the toll to journalists.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Twenty of the wounded have been admitted to Beledweyne hospitals, while another 20 are in critical condition, prompting a request for their airlift to Mogadishu for advanced medical treatment,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Hirshabelle includes Beledweyne, which is the capital of the Hiran region and has been the centre of the Somali government&#39;s latest military offensive against extremists from East Africa&#39;s al-Qaeda affiliate, al-Shabaab.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Images on social media showed black smoke billowing and a smashed truck cab blazing at the checkpoint.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Dr Suleyman Abdi Ali, the director of Beledweyne general hospital, said the bodies of 10 victims were brought to his hospital.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;There was no immediate claim of responsibility from al-Shabaab, which often carries out such attacks and controls parts of Somalia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It was a truck loaded with explosive devices that forcefully passed through the government-manned checkpoint, and a pickup vehicle belonging to security personnel was chasing it when it exploded,” witness Abdikadir Arba, who said he was about 200 metres away and was one of the first responders, told the Associated Press by phone.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jun/10/somalia-attack-al-shabaab-mogadishu-people-killed&quot;>;In June nine people were killed in an attack claimed by al-Shabaab at an upmarket restaurant in the Somali capital, Mogadishu&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Those killed at the popular Pearl restaurant were six civilians and three soldiers, police said.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 01:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[The former refugee who wants to cut immigration, and become the first female Dutch PM]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/23/dilan-yesilgoz-zegerius-former-refugee-wants-cut-immigration-first-female-dutch-pm]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T16:30:38Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52ff6fc8746844206a58b9b0af0b5683709996cd/0_65_4250_2550/master/4250.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b3dbe180466dd4c7c68c8d70be9d16c5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Dilan Yeşilgöz-Zegerius at podium&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;She is a former child refugee who wants to reduce immigration, has opened the door to the far right and could be the Netherlands&#39; first female prime minister. At a packed party conference in Rotterdam on Saturday, Dilan Yeşilgöz-Zegerius, leader of the People&#39;s Party for Freedom and Democracy (VVD), launched her campaign for November&#39;s elections with a call for liberty and security.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“From my parents, I learned to cherish freedom and stand up for others when their freedom was threatened,” she said. “但我们面临着失去更多‘氧气’的局面，彼此之间的理解越来越少，政治运作也越来越缺乏信任。 It&#39;s not for nothing that our manifesto is called: giving space, defining borders.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;For 13 years, the VVD, under prime minister Mark Rutte, has been custodian of the Netherlands, a small country which has punched above its weight in international trade and politics. Where it will go &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/08/mark-rutte-resigns-dutch-coalition-government-over-asylum-row&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;after him? &lt;/a>;Will it move to the right, in coalition with some &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dutchnews.nl/2023/09/whats-all-the-fuss-about-the-far-right-in-the-netherlands/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;extremist elements&lt;/a>;; will it try a radical tack under “centrist outsider” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/21/how-anti-establishment-parties-could-shape-europe-this-autumn&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;Pieter Omtzigt&lt;/a>;; or will it look left, to Frans Timmermans, former European Commission vice-president, in a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dutchnews.nl/2023/08/timmermans-wants-a-united-left-for-green-and-social-justice/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;green-left alliance&lt;/a>;?&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In a splintered political landscape, where a government will be formed by a coalition of three or more parties, leadership is a primary theme. For a generation, this will be the first election where Rutte does not end up automatically in charge, and yesterday Yeşilgöz-Zegerius, 46, who has been justice minister since January 2022, made her pitch to bright lights, streamers and the Dolly Parton song 9 to 5.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;As a councillor, she was a guest on all the programmes your average MP would kill to appear on&lt;/p>; &lt;footer>; &lt;cite>;Sheila Sitalsing, political journalist &lt;/cite>; &lt;/footer>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Raoul du Pré, political editor at the national daily &lt;em>;De&lt;/em>; &lt;em>;Volkskrant&lt;/em>;, said: “Of course, the VVD hopes she has the ideal profile.她是一位具有[移民]背景的女性，在很大程度上表现为白手起家。小时候，她逃到了荷兰，抓住了机会，现在正在前往总理官邸的路上。 That&#39;s the story.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Even before she became justice minister, Yeşilgöz-Zegerius had built an astonishing media profile. On a talk show in 2016, she showed her grandmother Sara&#39;s Louis Vuitton bag and told how she and her &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vvdamsterdam.nl/nieuws/21034/de-vrije-amsterdammer-dilan-yesilgoz-zegerius&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;politically active&lt;/a>; Turkish Kurdish parents had fled Turkey when she was eight. They took a “rickety” boat from Bodrum to Kos with what fitted in that bag, then settled in Amersfoort, 30 miles south-west of Amsterdam.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;By the time she was elected to parliament in 2017, after working as a VVD councillor, she had 45 TV appearances under her belt. Political journalist Sheila Sitalsing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.parool.nl/nederland/amsterdamse-politici-over-oud-collega-dilan-yesilgoz-in-den-haag-steeds-verder-naar-rechts-getrokken~bd2324dd/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;said&lt;/a>;: “As a councillor, she&#39;s been a guest on all the programmes your average MP would kill to appear on.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Yeşilgöz-Zegerius started her career with the Dutch Socialist party, then the Labour party, but found her feet in the centre-right VVD.她欣然接受因禁止街头骚扰而被称为“穿高跟鞋的斗牛犬”的感觉，并公开谈论了她的婚姻、与免疫系统疾病的斗争以及对生孩子的犹豫。去年，她在电视直播中剪掉了一绺头发——从后面选择一部分——以支持伊朗妇女。 “She&#39;s a talk show darling,” says du Pré.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As justice minister, she has criticised the “woke agenda”, extreme-right politicians and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dutchnews.nl/2022/09/justice-minister-slams-wokeism-extreme-right-and-conspiracy-theorists-in-democracy-speech/&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;conspiracy theorists,&lt;/a>; and launched a Europe-wide anti-crime drive. When the government fell in a row over immigration, she said family reunification should be restricted, arguing that she would not have had the chances she had in a country with more refugees.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Recently, she &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/50650867/vvd-lijsttrekker-yesilgoz-sluit-samenwerking-met-pvv-niet-op-voorhand-uit&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;told rightwing tabloid &lt;em>;De Telegraaf&lt;/em>; that,&lt;/a>; unlike Rutte, she would not rule out forming a coalition with &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/mar/08/can-geert-wilders-be-more-than-netherlands-far-right-agitator-in-chief&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;Geert Wilders&#39;s PVV&lt;/a>;, the far-right and anti-immigration party, and she repeated this today.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Carola Schoor of Leiden University&#39;s politics programme said: “She&#39;s a tough lady.很多人喜欢她。 And she has an agenda that will appeal to people who maybe &lt;em>;don&#39;t&lt;/em>; want a woman, or someone from Turkey, as prime minister.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But this tactic could backfire, said Léonie de Jonge, assistant politics professor at Groningen University. “Lots of research shows that when the centre-right tries to compete with the far right, voters go with the original and not with the copy,” she said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Meanwhile, although Yeşilgöz-Zegerius has called for a more “listening” government, she will want to distance herself from the VVD&#39;s legacy: a childcare benefits fiasco in which thousands of people, often dual-nationals, were incorrectly labelled fraudsters;非法收集政府数据； and earthquakes caused by gas extraction.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;After her speech, as she stood in an immaculate pink suit and heels surrounded by press, she was asked how she rated her chances of becoming the first female Dutch PM. “我不知道，但我正在尽力，”她说。 “It&#39;s up to the voter.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 00:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Nagorno-Karabakh: food and other aid arrives as talks resume]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/23/nagorno-karabakh-food-and-other-aid-arrives-as-talks-resume-azerbaijan-armenia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T16:36:29Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e05b4598fccd031769536c091aa8782d6983da0e/0_146_4385_2632/master/4385.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=01f472522ca9eb44da3d636c73db37ed&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;A Red Cross convoys passing next to a stopped humanitarian convoys for Nagorno-Karabakh.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;A Red Cross aid convoy headed to Nagorno-Karabakh on Saturday, the first since Azerbaijan retook the breakaway region three days ago, as ethnic Armenians there complained of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/23/nagorno-karabakh-talks-separatists-lay-down-arms-amid-fears-of-refugee-crisis&quot;>;being abandoned&lt;/a>; by the world.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Armenians of Karabakh, which is internationally recognised as part of Azerbaijan, were forced to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/20/nagorno-karabakh-death-toll-azerbaijan-armenia-attack-conflict-russia-us&quot;>;declare a ceasefire&lt;/a>; on 20 September after a lightning 24-hour military operation by the much larger Azerbaijani military.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Under the terms of the ceasefire, Russia&#39;s defence ministry said the Armenian fighters had begun handing over their weapons to Azerbaijan – including more than 800 guns and six armoured vehicles – under Russian supervision. Moscow has about 2,000 peacekeepers in the area.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Azerbaijani officials resumed talks on Saturday with Samvel Shahramanyan, the head of the self-styled Republic of Artsakh, as the Armenians call Karabakh, Azerbaijani media reported, but no further information was immediately available.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The mountainous region is home to about 120,000 Armenians, many of who have been without adequate food or fuel supplies for months due to an effective blockade by Azerbaijani forces.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Russia said it had delivered more than 50 tonnes of food and other aid to Karabakh.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) said it had supplied 28,000 nappies as well as blankets and fuel. A Reuters witness saw a small ICRC aid convoy approaching Armenia&#39;s border with Azerbaijan on Saturday afternoon but then journalists were ordered to leave before the trucks crossed the frontier.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;6ad80ffde4598f82875fe2f7b82ae1af4f3ebf78&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/6ad80ffde4598f82875fe2f7b82ae1af4f3ebf78/0_190_5692_3415/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;US senator, Gary Peters, observing the Lachin corridor from the Armenian side of the border near the town of Kornidzor.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;US senator, Gary Peters, said the situation required international observers and transparency from Azerbaijan.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Alain Jocard/AFP/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;More than 20 other aid trucks, bearing Armenian number plates, have been lined up along a nearby roadside since July. Azerbaijan said at the time this convoy amounted to a “provocation” and an attack on its territorial integrity.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Azerbaijan wants to integrate the long-contested region of Karabakh and has promised to protect the Armenians&#39; rights but says they are free to leave if they prefer. Armenians say they fear they will be persecuted if they stay.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Azerbaijan&#39;s interior ministry said on Saturday its main task was ensuring the safety of the Armenian civilian population and that it was providing them with tents, hot food and medical assistance.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We are also working on issuing documents to the Armenian population, passports and so on,” ministry spokesperson Elshad Hajiyev told Reuters. “There are already people who have applied to us.“&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;US senator Gary Peters, who visited the Armenia-Azerbaijan border on Saturday, said the situation in Karabakh required international observers and transparency from Azerbaijan.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I think the world needs to know exactly what&#39;s happening in there,” Peters, a Democrat from Michigan, told reporters. “We&#39;ve heard from the Azerbaijani government that there&#39;s nothing to see, nothing to worry about, but if that&#39;s the case then we should allow international observers in to see.”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-atom-id=&quot;b7e8c6f5-858f-4b80-801f-5cbd04ea21e0&quot; data-atom-type=&quot;media&quot;>; &lt;div>; &lt;div style=&quot;font-size:0&quot;>; __YOUTUBE_MEDIA_PLACEHOLDER_b7e8c6f5-858f-4b80-801f-5cbd04ea21e0__ &lt;iframe id=&quot;gu-video-youtube-b7e8c6f5-858f-4b80-801f-5cbd04ea21e0&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/Vm-NssYCXP8?modestbranding=1&amp;amp;showinfo=0&amp;amp;rel=0&amp;amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;amp;embed_config=%7B%22disableAds%22%3Atrue%2C%22nonPersonalizedAd%22%3Atrue%2C%22restrictedDataProcessor%22%3Atrue%2C%22adsConfig%22%3A%7B%22adTagParameters%22%3A%7B%22cmpGdpr%22%3A1%7D%7D%7D&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen>;&lt;/iframe>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Armenia, which lost a 2020 war to Azerbaijan over the region, has prepared space for tens of thousands of Armenians from Karabakh, including at hotels near the border, though the prime minister, Nikol Pashinyan, said he did not want them to leave their homes unless it was &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/armenian-pm-hopes-ethnic-armenians-can-remain-in-nagorno-karabakh-azerbaijan&quot;>;absolutely necessary&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Azerbaijan launched its “anti-terrorist” operation on Tuesday against Nagorno-Karabakh after some of its troops were killed in what Baku said were separatist attacks.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Karabakh region was more militarised than Baku realised, Hikmet Hajiyev, a foreign policy adviser to Azerbaijan&#39;s president, said on social media on Saturday, publishing a list of weapons and ammunition that had been seized in the past three days, including four tanks, 300 explosives and 441 mortar shells.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Armenui Karapetyan, an Armenian in Karabakh, said he was now homeless, holding just a few possessions and a photograph of his 24-year-old son who died in 2020, after leaving his home in the village of Kusapat.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Today we were thrown out into the street – they made us vagabonds,” Karapetyan told Armenia A1+, a partner of Reuters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“What can I say?我们生活在一个不公平、被遗弃的世界。我无话可说了。我为我们孩子的鲜血感到难过。 I feel sorry for our lands for which our boys sacrificed their lives, and today … I miss the grave of my son.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Thousands of Karabakh Armenians have massed at the airport seeking the protection of Russian peacekeepers there.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Svetlana Alaverdyan, from Arajadzor, said she had fled with just the clothes on her back after gun fights gripped the village.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“They were shooting on the right, they were shooting on the left – we went out one after another, without taking clothes,” she told Armenia A1+.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 24 Sep 2023 00:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Not just for summer’: France turns to rosé wine as a year-round tipple]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/sep/23/not-just-for-summer-france-turns-to-rose-wine-as-a-year-round-tipple]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-23T13:55:14Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/da98a7196743f509e4fbef80335a7dd981275541/470_815_7482_4489/master/7482.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=943a3b8836edc26c23e78b4c2d7d5299&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Rosé is especially popular with young people in France&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;For the French, a glass of chilled blush rosé was once considered a delicate but not entirely serious “swimming pool drink”; a summer &lt;em>;apéritif &lt;/em>;for lightweight, often female, tipplers.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Real wine lovers would select a red heavy with tannins, or a traditional white – both considered the true expression of French &lt;em>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/may/19/theres-more-to-wine-than-terroir&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;terroir&lt;/a>;,&lt;/em>; the untranslatable concept encompassing not just the soil in which the vines grow&lt;strong>; &lt;/strong>;but also the natural, geological climatic and cultural elements associated with it.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But tastes are changing.法国的红酒销量正在下​​降。 Drinkers are turning to lighter, lower alcohol wines, but what has surprised winemakers most of all is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/food/2021/nov/12/try-rose-in-winter-itll-grow-on-you-rose-wine-in-winter-fiona-beckett&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;rise of rosé&lt;/a>;, now enjoying year-round popularity.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Even former president &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/nicolas-sarkozy&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;Nicolas Sarkozy&lt;/a>; – who has reportedly never let a drop of alcohol pass his lips – and his wife, Carla Bruni, have joined the fashion. The power couple recently launched a rosé wine called Roseblood from their Château d&#39;Estoublon vineyard in the Bouches-du-Rhône, acquired last year.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While bottles of red remain the jewel in France&#39;s global winemaking crown and 40% of annual production&lt;strong>;, &lt;/strong>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/feb/19/red-wine-on-the-brink-not-if-i-have-anything-to-do-with-it#:~:text=Consumption of red wine in,are eating less red meat.&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;domestic demand has plummeted&lt;/a>; to half of what it was in the 1990s. Industry experts say people eating less meat and drinking less alcohol means there are fewer occasions calling for a bottle of red.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Independent winemaker Thomas Montagne, whose Luberon vineyard in southern France produces red, white and rosé wines, said: “In the 1990s we had the &#39;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2003/aug/25/health.france&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;French paradox&lt;/a>;&#39;, where studies showed that red wine was good for your health. Now people, especially the young, are turning to rosé wines, which are easier to drink, contain fewer tannins and feel more festive.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The French have noted a general decline in their wine drinking for decades.国家葡萄酒专业委员会 CNIV 在 2019 年报告称，目前每人每年的平均葡萄酒消费量为 40 升，而 1975 年为 100 升。法国每年生产近 3800 万百升（8.3 亿加仑）葡萄酒。 After reds are whites at 29% of bottles, rosés at 19% and champagne and sparkling wine at 12%.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A 2022 survey by pollsters Kantar found 18- to 35-year-olds less interested in wine than previous generations, with 47% of wine drunk by those over 55. Only 7% was drunk by 18- to 24-year-olds and 21% by 25- to 39-year-olds. The survey also found red wine drinking had dropped by almost a third in the previous decade when other studies showed meat-eating had dropped by 12% in France.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;bd9cd3ceb0b19c26ab2152406ea1f8077eeb38ad&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/bd9cd3ceb0b19c26ab2152406ea1f8077eeb38ad/0_136_5200_3121/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Vineyards in Provence, as pictured, have led the rise of rosé – mostly drunk by the French themselves&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Vineyards in Provence, as pictured, have led the rise of rosé – mostly drunk by the French themselves.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Andrea Pistolesi/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Burgundy vineyards now produce half as much red wine as they did 20 years ago but have increased white wine production, a spokesperson for regional winemakers told the &lt;em>;Observer&lt;/em>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But it is the popularity of rosé that is raising eyebrows. “桃红葡萄酒通常被认为是泳池酒，但在过去的几年里，它不仅在夏天饮用，而且全年都可以饮用。 I was surprised to discover it was being drunk in winter,” the spokesperson said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The drop in the popularity of red wine is due to an erosion of clientele – with people drinking less overall – and because the occasions to do so are disappearing. The younger generations are eating less meat and shunning reds in favour of whites or rosés.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Contrary to the myth that it is produced by mixing red and white wines – illegal in French wine production – the colour of rosé is a result of the vinification process.红葡萄浸渍的时间长短决定了红葡萄酒和桃红葡萄酒的颜色。对于红葡萄酒，黑葡萄需要浸泡更长时间。 The process is the same for rosé except the fruit is left for less time, giving a lighter colour.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Around 42% of French rosés are produced in the Provence region and, while exports are growing, most is consumed by domestic drinkers.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brice Eymar, director general of the Conseil interprofessionnel des vins de Provence, the group that represents regional wine growers, said rosés were shaking off their image as an industry lightweight.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Because it is a wine drunk during the holidays, this has stuck in the head of consumers.但普罗旺斯一直在努力扩大其醉酒的时间。 Rosé is not just for summer,” he told French radio.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Montagne, however, thinks the taste for rosé has peaked. “我认为我们已经看到桃红葡萄酒的销售趋于稳定。在过去的五六年里，白葡萄酒的销量有所上升，”他说。 He believes red and white wines are the true expression of French &lt;em>;terroir&lt;/em>; and the decline in popularity of red wines reflects a change in French and European culture, which he regrets.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“People no longer sit down to family meals, and campaigns against alcoholism have hit quality wines in favour of beers,” he said. “But it makes no sense, because wines are generally drunk at mealtimes while young people drink beer all day long.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On a lighter note, he said: “Wine is meant to be drunk for pleasure. Of course there is an art and an aesthetic to it, but what will kill the industry is taking it all too seriously.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 23 Sep 2023 22:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>